<chapter xml:id="ch-3-floor-function" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Floor Function</title>

  <introduction>
  
  <definition>
  The <term>floor</term> of a real number <m>x</m>,
  denoted <m>\lfloor x \rfloor</m>, is the greatest integer less than or equal to <m>x</m>.
  The floor is also denoted <m>[x]</m>, mostly in older texts.
  Related functions include:
  <ol>
  <li> <m>\lceil x \rceil = \min \{ n \in \bbZ : n \geq x \}</m>,
  the <term>ceiling</term> of <m>x</m> </li>
  <li> <m>\{x\} = x - \lfloor x \rfloor</m>,
  the <term>fractional part</term> of <m>x</m> </li>
  </ol>
	</definition>


  </introduction>

